"date": "1945-11-23", "dates": ["1945-11-23"], "description": ["The MONITORLEADER MACOMB rUBLiftHING COMPANY latetstT\u00dfS iSSfLisMSSVWS 22nI0im At Mount Otam MltfcUw BUSDfEM CIRCULATION CLAMOTIED JOB PRINT IXO Mount Clmono 45W Connecting All Dprtmnt MEMBER OF Til ASSOCIATED rESS CLIENT 07 UNITED MMI sjrrsjirc Ji \u00df i a to f MMmb County r w SJS iIESrISS cAueo 2S L Sidg Dotrolt 1 _ AFTER THE DELUGE Readers whose memory of the theater or movies spans 10 years or so may recall a play called The Deluge It was the story of a group of people a smalltown group full of social political and persona animosities who took refuge from a flood in a water tight basement Though in temporary safety all faced death from suffocation in their unventilated refuge And as breathing became more difficult and death drew nearer their enmities seemed less and less important Two by two they resolved their differences admitted the good points of their opponents views and char acters and composed their souls to meet their im minent fate At last the oxygen in the room was nearly ex hausted Preferring quick drowning to suffocation one of the characters threw open the door in expec tation of a torrent of water But the flood had"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2024-01-16T21:37:17.784Z", "group": ["ndnp/mimtptc", "central-michigan-university-clark-historical-library-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn96077289/1945-11-23/ed-1/?sp=6", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:mimtptc:batch_mimtptc_alma_ver01:data:sn96077289:00414187638:1945112301:1111/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg#h=321&w=243", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:mimtptc:batch_mimtptc_alma_ver01:data:sn96077289:00414187638:1945112301:1111/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=643&w=486", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/mimtptc/batch_mimtptc_alma_ver01/data/sn96077289/00414187638/1945112301/1111.xm